(15, 'Chairperson', 'Chairperson,National Institute of Technology.', '<table cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="height:272px; width:500px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img alt="" src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/chairman.jpg" style="height:258px; width:179px" /></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Dr. A. Sivathanu Pillai,Chairperson Board of Governors</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>National Institute of Technology,Kurukshetra</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Born in 1947, <strong> Dr. A. Sivathanu Pillai</strong> graduated in Electrical Engineering from Madras University in 1969, Management Development from Harvard Business School USA, and Ph. D. from Pune University.<br />\r\nDr. Pillai joined Space Science &amp; Technology Centre, Thiruvananthapuram in 1969 where he significantly contributed to the evolution of the 10-year space profile of the country and development of the four stage rocket motors and rocket systems. Under the leadership of Dr. A P J Abdul Kalam, he worked as a Core Team Member of SLV-3 whose first stage subsequently became the booster of Agni missile.&nbsp; Later, he became a Member of the Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle (PSLV) study team for evolution of PSLV mission. Afterwards, he was elevated to the prestigious position of Technical Advisor to Prof. Satish Dhawan, Chairman ISRO.&nbsp; In 1986, Dr. Pillai joined DRDO as the Programme Director, Integrated Guided Missile Development Programme (IGMDP), Hyderabad and made significant contributions to the development of Agni, Prithvi, Nag, and Akash Missiles.&nbsp; He was also Associate Director, DRDL where he made outstanding contributions to the development of critical technologies using network of academic institutions, R&amp;D laboratories, and industries for the national missile programme. As spin offs from missile technologies, Dr. Pillai led the development of many societal products, specially light weight calipers for polio affected children.<br />\r\nHe was appointed to the coveted position of Chief Controller (Research &amp; Development) at DRDO HQrs, New Delhi in 1996 and provided leadership to the development of missile technologies &amp; projects, ranges, navel systems, and International Collaborations.&nbsp; For his path breaking contributions to National missile technology developments, DRDO honoured Dr. Pillai by conferring him status of &lsquo;<em>Distinguished Scientist</em>&rsquo; in 1999. He is globally regarded for conceiving and transforming into reality the present most advanced BRAHMOS-Supersonic Cruise Missile of the country which is the National pride of India in the world and Dr. Pillai is regarded as Father of BRAHMOS.&nbsp;<br />\r\nDr. Pillai has published a large number of papers in reputed international / national journals and conference proceedings, and authored / co-authored number of books which are sources of knowledge enriching, acquisition, and inspiration on emerging technology areas. He is a recipient of several prestigious awards such as &lsquo;<em>DRDO Scientist of the year</em> (1988)&rsquo;, &lsquo;<em>Vikram Sarabhai Research Award </em>(1991)&rsquo;, &lsquo;<em>Dr. Davidson Frame Award for Project Leadership from University of Technology &amp; Management, USA </em>(2001)&rsquo;, &lsquo;Padmashri, Government of India (2002)&rsquo;, &lsquo;<em>OISCA (Organisation for Industrial, Spiritual &amp; Cultural Advancement) International</em>, Japan (2003)&rsquo;, &lsquo;Performance Excellence Award of DRDO for BrahMos (2005)&rsquo;, &lsquo;<em>Raja Rammohan Puraskar </em>(2006)&rsquo;<em>, &lsquo;Lokmanya Tilak Award </em>(2007)<em>&rsquo;, &lsquo;Dr Y. Nayudamma Memorial Award </em>(2008)&rsquo;, and &lsquo;DRDO <em>Technology Leadership Award </em>(2009)<em>&rsquo;</em> &nbsp;for his outstanding contributions to indigenous competitive technology development. Dr. Pillai is an &lsquo;<em>A Level Certified Project Director&rsquo;</em> recognized by International Project Management Association, Switzerland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recognizing his commendable R &amp; D contributions and leadership to research promotion in network mode with academic institutions, many leading institutions such as <em>Andhra University, Bharathiar University, Mangalore University, The Tamil Nadu Dr. M.G.R. Medical University, Scientific Council of St. Petersburg State Marine Technical University, Russia, Sathyabama University of Science and Technology, Avinashilingam Institute of Higher Education for Woman, Pravara Rural University, Thapar University, and National Institute of Technology, Kurukshetra</em> have honored Dr. Pillai by conferring him honorary degree of &lsquo;<em>Doctor of Science (Honoris Causa)&rsquo;.</em>&nbsp; The Moscow University of &ldquo;Security, Defence and Law Enforcement&rdquo; has honored Dr. Pillai with the Order of the Peter the Great and the Academician of the University. Dr. Pillai is Fellow of Indian National Academy of Engineering, Astronautical Society of India, Honorary Fellow of the Association of Minimal Access Surgeons of India (FAMS) and International Project Management Association. In addition, he is member of many professional societies like IEEE, Aeronautical Society of India (AeSI), Instrument Society of India, and International Association of Business Leaders (USA).&nbsp; Dr. Pillai has visited and interacted with scientific and technological organizations in more than 30 countries.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', '["18","17","16","13"]', 'sidenav'),
(16, 'Director', 'Prof. Anand Mohan joined as the Director of National Institute of Technology (NIT), Kurukshetra on 3rd June, 2011. Prior to his present assignment, he was Professor of Electronics Engineering at Institute of Technology, Banaras Hindu University where he has held as several important administrative positions namely Member of Executive Council, Head of the Department of Electronics Engineering, Coordinator, Centre for Research in Microprocessor Applications (established by MHRD), and Incharge, University Science Instrumentation Centre.', '<table border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="height:270px; width:500px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img alt="" src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/photo/5000.jpg" style="height:256px; width:200px" /></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Prof. Anand Mohan</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Director,<br />\r\n			National Institute of Technology,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Kurukshetra</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prof. <em>Anand Mohan</em></strong> joined as the Director of National Institute of Technology (NIT), Kurukshetra on 3rd June, 2011. Prior to his present assignment, he was Professor of Electronics Engineering at Institute of Technology, Banaras Hindu University where he has held as several important administrative positions namely Member of Executive Council, Head of the Department of Electronics Engineering, Coordinator, Centre for Research in Microprocessor Applications (established by MHRD), and Incharge, University Science Instrumentation Centre. &nbsp;Prof. Mohan has 35 years rich experience of serving both academia and industry in various capacities. Besides this, he has been Member of several apex administrative bodies like Executive Council / Governing Council / University Court of JNU, New Delhi, Mizoram University, Aizawl, HBTI, Kanpur, IET, Lucknow, Visitor&rsquo;s nominee of IGNOU, and Chancellor&rsquo;s nominee of Rajasthan Technical University, Kota. Besides these additional assignments, he is Member of Research Advisory Committee of All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMs), New Delhi and also served for 7 years as Chairman of Armament Sensors &amp; Electronics (ASE) Panel under ARMREB, DRDO, Ministry of Defence, Govt. of India. Prof. Mohan has been associated with several important academic and research advisory committees of DST, UGC, CSIR, and AICTE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prof. Mohan</strong></em> obtained Ph. D., PG, and UG degrees in Electronics Engineering from Banaras Hindu University in 1994, 1977, and 1973 respectively. He has made notable contributions to the academic and research development in Electronics Engineering at Banaras Hindu University by creating dedicated research groups of eminent academic experts from the country and abroad. He conducted high quality research in the emerging areas like <em>fault tolerant / survivable system design</em>, <em>information security</em>, and <em>embedded systems</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact Details:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Phone No. Tel:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 01744-233201,233204, 238083</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fax No.:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 01744-238494</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Email- ID:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; director@nitkkr.ac.in</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Residence:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A-1,NIT Campus, Kurukshetra </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '["18","17","15","13","7"]', 'sidenav');
