luding HRA) not to exceed Rs. 25000/- per annum Standard deduction allowed to salaried people.</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; text-align: justify; width: 116px;">Marks secured in the first semester examination.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			The DPI of the state from which the student has passed the qualifying examination<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; width: 86px;">3. National Scholarship<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; text-align: center; width: 115px;">-</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; text-align: center; width: 158px;">-</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; width: 73px;">Rs. 300/- per month for boarders and Rs. 120/- per month for day scholars<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; text-align: justify; width: 155px;">60% or marks in the aggregate in the qualifying examination and parents income not to Rs. 25000/- per annum (excluding HRA) standard deduction allowed to salaried people.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; width: 116px;">Result of the examination which the student has passed as the qualifying examination<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; width: 86px;">4. National Scholarship for children of School Teachers<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; text-align: center; width: 115px;">-</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; text-align: center; width: 158px;">-</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 267px; width: 73px;">Rs. 125/- per month for boarders and Rs. 100/- per month for day scholars<br />\r\n			<br />\r\