(66, 'R&D Computer Department', 'Research and Development Computer Department | National Institute of Technology.', '<h1>R&amp;D COMPUTER ENGINEERING DEPARTMENT</h1>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>B. Tech Degree</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The department has been offering B.Tech. Degree Course in Computer Engineering since 1987 with an intake of 33 students. A sound theoretical and practical work prepares the students in wider field of Computer Engineering to take up challenging jobs in the area of :-</p>\r\n\r\n			<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Systems Software Development</td>\r\n						<td rowspan="4">\r\n						<p><a href="http://nitkkr.ac.in/77comP.htm" target="_top"><img alt="&lt;&lt; Click Here &lt;&lt;" src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/complab.jpg" style="height:82px; width:125px" /></a></p>\r\n						</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Application Software Development</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Computer Networking.</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n						<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n\r\n			<p>The department has also offering B.Tech. Degree Courses in Information Technology since 2006 with present intake of 84 student.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>There is 100% placement of all students through campus and our students are&nbsp;&nbsp; placed in reputed IT companies like Microsoft, IBM, TCS, HCL, Hughes, Perrot Systems, DRDO, CMC, VSNL, Wipro, Google, CDOT, Satyam, Oracle, HP, Samsung, Infosys etc.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>M. Tech Degree</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>M. Tech. Degree Course in Computer Engineering (<strong>part-time</strong>) has been introduced from 1996 for sponsored candidates of the NIT, Kurukshetra.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>M. Tech. Degree Course in Computer Engineering (<strong>Regular</strong>) has been introduced from 2009.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Degree of Doctor of Philosophy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Facilities for research are offered in the department on various topics leading to Doctor of Philosophy in Computer Engineering.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Research Facilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Faculty is specialized in the department for advanced studies and research exit in the following fields:-</p>\r\n\r\n			<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Operating Systems</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Computer Networks</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Distributed Computing</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Software Engineering</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Object Oriented Technology</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n						<td>Database and Data Mining</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Hardware Facilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><strong>Rack Servers :- </strong>Processor Intel Xeon 3 GHz, 4GB RAM, DVD Combo Drive running windows Server 2003 - Two Nos.</li>\r\n				<li><strong>AMD Optron Based Servers</strong> :- Processor Intel Xeon 3 GHz, 8GB RAM, DVD Combo Drive running windows Server 2003 - Two Nos.</li>\r\n				<li><strong>Standalone Servers :- </strong>AMD Optron Based Servers having 2GB RAM, DVD Combo Drive running windows Server 2003 - Four Nos.</li>\r\n				<li><strong>Desktop Computers</strong>\r\n				<ol>\r\n					<li>Intel Pentium Core 2 Duo based configuration with 3 GHz, 250 GB HDD, 2GB RAM, DVD Combo Drive, 17&quot; Flat Monitor - 200 Nos.</li>\r\n					<li>Intel Pentium Dual Core based configuration with 3 GHz, 250GB HDD, 2GB RAM, DVD Combo Drive, 17&quot; Flat Monitor - 100 Nos.</li>\r\n				</ol>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li>The department has <strong>seven LCD projectors</strong> which have been installed in the Seminar room, Conference room, lecturers rooms and laboratories of the department.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>MHRD Project in the Department</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>MODROB Scheme titled &quot;Modernization of Department of Computer Centre&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Amount Rs. 15 Lakh 2003-05, Principal Investigator Dr. Mayank Dave.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Some computer equipment purchased under this scheme includes</p>\r\n\r\n			<blockquote>\r\n			<p><strong>HP ML 150 Server -</strong> Processor Intel Xeon 3 GHz, 1GB RAM, RAID 1 HDD 36 GB x2 with DAT Drive, DVD Combo Drive running Linux - One Nos.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Acer Altos Server -</strong> Processor Intel Xeon 3 GHz, 1GB RAM, RAID 3 HDD 36 GB x3 with DAT Drive, CD Drive running Windows 2000 Server - One Nos.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Desktop Computers -</strong> Intel Pentium 3.0 GHz with HT, 40 GB HDD, 512 mb ram, DVD Combo Drive, 1.44 MB FDD, 17&quot; Flat Monitor - Five Nos.</p>\r\n			</blockquote>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Library Facilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The department has its own library (shared with Electronics &amp; Communication Engineering) having more than 2000 books in different areas.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'null', 'sidenav'),
(67, 'R&D Physics Department', 'Research and Development Physics Department | National Institute of Technology.', '<h1>RESEARCH PHYSICS DEPARTMENT</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Department has research facilities in various fields of experimental and theoretical Physics. The major fields are:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Solid State Nuclear Track Detectors (SSNTDs) and Nuclear Track Filters</td>\r\n			<td rowspan="4"><a href="http://nitkkr.ac.in/84physics.htm" target="_top"><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/physicslab3.jpg" style="height:93px; width:125px" /></a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Nanotechnology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Instrumentation and Sensors</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Conducting Polymers</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Electrical Properties of Industrial Polymers&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Health and Radiation Physics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Radon Mapping</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Nuclear Physics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Spintronics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Experimental condensed matter Physics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">Consultancy is available in Optical Instrumentation, FTIR spectroscopy, SRC, SPM, SEM and Dielectric Properties of cables, Battery Technology, and related materials</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Major Research Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Scanning Probe Microscope (AFM, STM, MFM)</li>\r\n	<li>Scanning Electron Microscope (SEM)</li>\r\n	<li>X-Ray Diffractometer (XRD)</li>\r\n	<li>X-Ray Fluorescence (XRF)</li>\r\n	<li>FTIR</li>\r\n	<li>Vacuum Coating Unit</li>\r\n	<li>Sputtering Unit</li>\r\n	<li>UV VIS-Spectrometer</li>\r\n	<li>Cryogenic System</li>\r\n	<li>Source Meter, LCR Meters</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>R &amp; D Projects (in progress)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1.</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>&quot;Low Temperature Relaxation Investigations in Energetic Ion Irradiated Engineering Polymers&quot; </strong>Funded by <strong>DRDO, New Delhi.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dr. J.K. Quamara, Professor in Physics Department, Rs 14.87 Lakh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2.</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>&quot;Synthesis and Characterization of Multiferroic Materials with Magnetoelectric Properities&quot; </strong>Funded by <strong>D.S.T., New Delhi</strong>. <strong>....(Recommended)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Dr. Anurag Gaur, Assistant Professor in Physics Department, Rs. 17 Lakh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Research Publications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:61%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp; Published in</strong></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Total&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>In Last 4 Yrs</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp; International Journals</td>\r\n			<td>116</td>\r\n			<td>45</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp; National Journals</td>\r\n			<td>46</td>\r\n			<td>12</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp; International/National Conf.</td>\r\n			<td>366</td>\r\n			<td>60</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp; Ph.D. awarded:</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>7</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'null', 'sidenav'),
(68, 'R&D Mathmatics Department', 'Research and Development Mathematics Department | National Institute of Technology.', '<h1>RESEARCH FACILITIES MATHEMATICS DEPARTMENT</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Members of the department guide research scholars for the degree of Doctor of Philosophy in addition to undertaking their own research work. Research facilities are available in the following areas :</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Non-linear elasticity</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Elastic waves</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Coupled stress theories</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Theory of elasticity</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Liquid dielectrics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Plasticity</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Non-Newtonain fluids</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Micromorphic materials</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Interaction of different fields like Thermoelasticity, Magnetothermoelasticity Electro-elastics of Mechanics, Granular Media.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Statics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Numerical Analysis</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Consultancy/Industrial Collaboration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The department offers research facilities in the following areas :</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Magnetic Fluids :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Preparation of Magnetic Fluids</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Mechanical devices based on magnetic fluid e.g. seals, bearing, energy convertors and magnetically coupled Hi-Fi speakers.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Medical Applications of Magnetic Fluids.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan="2"><strong>Semiconductors</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Deformation of Semiconductor and its applications to acoustic electronics</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan="2"><strong>Elastic, Dielectrics and Liquid Crystals</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Deformation analysis of various types of rubber sheets at different temperatures</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Applications of liquid crystals</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Operation Research and Mathematical Modelling</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Reliability models</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>Computer Aided Fluid Flow Problems.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'null', 'sidenav'),
