(75, 'Mathematics Department', 'National Institute of Technology.', '<h1>DEPARTMENT OF MATHEMATICS</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Aims &amp; Objective</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>To start M. Tech. Course in Computational Techniques and Modelling.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>To organize conferences and seminars in emerging area of Science &amp; Technology.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/dotGrey.gif" style="height:10px; width:16px" /></td>\r\n			<td>To lay thrust on research activities in vigor manner by way of fetching research projects from various funding agencies.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Papers published in Conferences/Seminars</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper entitled, &ldquo;Reliability and availability of a three unit stand by system with two types each of failure and repair&rdquo;, presented in National Conference on &lsquo;Applications of Mathematics in Engineering &amp; Technology&rsquo; MIMIT, Malout (Punjab) on 26-28th March, 2005 by Dr. D.V. Singh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper entitled, &ldquo;Cyclic Self Dual Codes&rdquo; published in Proc. of National Seminar on &lsquo;Applications of Mathematics in Science &amp; Technology&rsquo;, Jabalpur 2004 pp.1-10 by Dr. Jai Singh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Papers published in Journals</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper entitled, &ldquo;Numerical analysis of reliability and availability of the serial processes in butter-oil processing plant&rdquo;, published in International Journal of Quality and Reliability, 22(3), pp. 303-316, 2005 by Dr. Jai Singh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper entitled, &ldquo;&ldquo;Vibrations of a Cylindrical Cavity in an Elastic dielectric&rdquo; accepted for publication in the Journal of Mathematics and System Sciences scheduled for June 2005 by Dr. Kuldeep Kumar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Undergraduate &amp; Postgraduate Courses</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The department offers courses in Mathematics to both the Undergraduate and Postgraduate students of the Institute.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The aim is to equip the engineering students with modern concepts of Mathematics and Mechanics as applied in different engineering disciplines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Electives</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following electives are offered to students of the 7th and 8th semesters :</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Advanced Applied Mathematics-I</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced Applied Mathematics-II</p>\r\n', '["76","68"]', 'department'),
(76, 'Faculty Mathematics Department', 'National Institute of Technology.', '<h1>&nbsp;FACULTY MATHEMATICS DEPARTMENT</h1>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:76%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;<strong>Head of Department</strong></td>\r\n			<td colspan="2">&nbsp;<a href="http://nitkkr.ac.in/FacMaths.htm">Paras Ram</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan="2"><strong>Associate Professor</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;<a href="http://nitkkr.ac.in/FacMaths.htm">Paras Ram</a></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Ph.D.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Assistant Professor</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;<a href="http://nitkkr.ac.in/FacMaths.htm">Ms. Sarsvati Yadav</a></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Ph.D.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan="1">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '["76","68"]', 'sidenav'),
(77, 'Physics Department', 'National Institute of Technology.', '<h1>PHYSICS DEPARTMENT</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Aims &amp; Objectives of the department, Mission:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since fundamental principles of Physics form the very basis of Engineering and Technology, the department, therefore, aims at providing the necessary knowledge of Physics to the young engineers. The main activities of the Department are Under-graduate teaching, Post-graduate teaching, Research and Development programme.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Undergraduate Teaching</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the 1st&nbsp; and 2nd semester, the students of all B. Tech branches are given compulsory courses in Physics while a number of courses are offered as Non Departmental Electives in the 7th &amp; 8th semesters as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Department offers curricula consisting the basic principles of Physics besides emerging areas of Technology so as to provide necessary background to future Engineers.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:100%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="height: 263px; width: 77%;"><strong>Post-graduate Teaching</strong>\r\n\r\n			<p>The department runs a four-semester M.Tech programme in <strong>Instrumentation</strong> and <strong>Nanotechnology</strong>. The programmes are shared by other departments viz, Electrical Engg., Mechanical Engg., Electronics and Communication Engg. and Computer Engg. The inputs in Instrumentation stream are the candidates having the degree of M.Sc. (Physics) with two electronics papers, M.Sc. (Electronics), B.Tech. (Electronics), B.Tech. (Instrumentation), B.Tech. (Electrical) while in Nanotechnology stream jare the candidates having M.Sc, (physics), jM.Sc. j(Bio-science), B.Tech. j(Bio-Instrumentation) and all other B.Tech./BE degrees.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Other details can be found in the Institute&rsquo;s Brochure and Website from time to time. The Department has a vision to launch in future B.Tech in Engineering Physics and M.Sc. in Physics in order to meet the global technical demands and create a need based technical man power.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>For M.Tech. courses Department has procured the sophisticated instruments which include SEM, XRD, SRF, SPM, UV - vis spectrometer, sputtering unit.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height: 263px;"><a href="http://nitkkr.ac.in/80physics.htm" target="_top"><img src="http://nitkkr.ac.in/images/phylab01.jpg" style="float:right; height:82px; width:127px" /></a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Infrastructure details :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" style="width:80%">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width: 43%;">\r\n			<p><strong>Name of the Lab. Workshop</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 31%;">\r\n			<p><strong>Area</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 26%;">\r\n			<p><strong>Total Area (Sq.M)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width: 43%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Workshop</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 31%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;3.05 x 8.25</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 26%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 25.16</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width: 43%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; Junior Lab.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 31%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 15.83 x 8.25</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 26%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 130.60</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width: 43%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; (1)Dark Room</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 31%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 6.40 x 4.1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 26%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 26.24</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width: 43%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; (2)Dark room</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 31%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 6.40 x 4.1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="width: 26%;">\r\n			<p>&nbsp; 26.24</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="width: 43%;">\